---
sequenceDiagram
    participant Trader as Trader (Sender)
    participant Relay as Relay Node (EkweBox)
    participant Customer as Customer (Receiver)
    participant Executor as Execution Node
    participant Commit as Commit Node (Bitcoin L2)
    participant BTC as Bitcoin L1

    Trader->>Relay: 1. PAYMENT.REQUEST (LoRa/BLE)
    Note over Trader,Relay: Signed intent with amount, currency, TTL

    Relay->>Customer: 2. Gossip forward (BLE/Wi-Fi)
    Note over Relay,Customer: Store-and-forward via nearby relays

    Customer->>Relay: 3. PAYMENT.CONFIRM (signed)
    Note over Customer,Relay: Ed25519 signature, bounded validity

    Relay->>Executor: 4. Forward to Execution Node
    Executor->>Executor: 5. Run payment logic (WASM/zkVM)
    Executor->>Executor: 6. Generate ZK proof

    Executor->>Commit: 7. Submit receipt + proof
    Note over Executor,Commit: Batched with other receipts

    Commit->>BTC: 8. Periodic L1 anchoring
    Note over Commit,BTC: When online: zkRollup commitment

    Commit-->>Relay: 9. Settlement confirmation
    Relay-->>Trader: 10. Transaction finalized
    Relay-->>Customer: 10. Transaction finalized
